{"title":"Pipelines CPT: scaling-pipelines: Test description","type":"markdown","aggs":[],"params":{"fontSize":12,"openLinksInNewTab":false,"markdown":"# scaling-pipelines test

For test code by Khurram see: [tests/scaling-pipelines/](https://github.com/openshift-pipelines/performance/tree/master/tests/scaling-pipelines).

Test creates `total` PipelineRuns based on given yaml `template`, making sure at most `concurrency` of them is running at a moment. Test waits for all the PRs to finish (successfully or not).

Then we collect bunch of metrics about the PRs. Most importantly average durations for successful ones:

* **duration** = .status.completionTime - .metadata.creationTimestamp
* **pending** = .status.startTime - .metadata.creationTimestamp
* **running** = .status.completionTime - .status.startTime

We also collect various metrics from cluster's Prometheus and store some statistical measures for these. See [config/cluster_read_config.yaml](https://github.com/openshift-pipelines/performance/blob/master/config/cluster_read_config.yaml) for the list of what we are collecting."}}
